  "summary": "Interactions can t be interacted",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "1. summon interaction n n n2. Right click to this interaction n n n3. data get entity e[type interaction, limit 1, sort nearest] n n n4. There is not a NBT interaction n n n n n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Create a new Creative world with default settings.\n2. Open the chat and enter the command `/summon interaction ~ ~ ~` to summon an interaction entity at your current location.\n3. Position your character close to the interaction entity.\n4. Right-click on the interaction entity to attempt to interact with it.\n5. Open the chat again and enter the command `/data get entity @e[type=interaction,limit=1,sort=nearest]` to retrieve the NBT data of the nearest interaction entity.\n6. Observe that the NBT data does not contain any interaction-related information.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 1.21.8",
  "Observed Behavior": "When an interaction entity is summoned using the command `/summon interaction <x> <y> <z>`, it is expected to register player interactions (both left-click and right-click) and store the UUID of the last player to interact with it. However, the following issues occur:\n\n1. **No Interaction Recognition**: Right-clicking the interaction entity does not trigger any expected behavior, such as playing a sound or registering the interaction. The entity does not respond to player interactions at all, effectively making it non-functional.\n\n2. **Data Retrieval Failure**: When attempting to retrieve data from the interaction entity using the command `data get entity e[type=interaction, limit=1, sort=nearest]`, the expected NBT data (specifically the UUID of the last player to interact and the timestamp of the interaction) is not present. This indicates that the entity is not recording any interaction data.\n\n3. **Absence of NBT Tags**: The interaction entity lacks the necessary NBT tags that should normally be present after a player interacts with it. Specifically, the `player` and `timestamp` fields are missing, which are crucial for tracking interactions.\n\nThis behavior suggests a bug in the interaction entity's functionality, as it fails to behave as documented and expected within the game mechanics.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When an interaction entity is summoned using the command, it should be interactable by players. Specifically, when a player right-clicks on the interaction entity, the UUID of the player who interacted with it should be recorded, along with a timestamp of the interaction. Additionally, executing the command to retrieve the entity's data should return the expected NBT data, including the player's UUID and the timestamp, confirming that the interaction has been properly logged. If the interaction entity has the response property set to true, a punching sound should play upon left-clicking, and the player's arm should swing when right-clicking, indicating that the interaction is functioning as intended.",
